  "text": "In recent years, a number of attempts have been made to reduce preventable morbidity and mortality in hospitalised patients. Unfortunately, initiatives such as the medical emergency team (MET) concept and the Modified Early Warning Score 1 2 have not consistently led to decreases in hospital mortality, cardiac arrest and transfer to the intensive care unit (ICU). [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] Litvak et al [CITATION_5] have postulated that necessity for MET intervention implies either inadequate care or inappropriate triage to an inadequate care environment, suggesting that another approach is needed.",
